      • runFinal

        public void runFinal(PortInput[] inputs,
                     PortOutput[] outputs,
                     ExecutionContext exec)
              throws Exception
        Performs the execution on the input and (possibly) produces the output. The array elements of the inputs argument must be cast to specific classes. The class depends on the InputPortRole of the corresponding port (as described by NodeModel.getInputPortRoles(). If it is streamable (which can only be true for data ports), then the object can be cast to RowInput. If it's non streamable, then it's an instance of PortObjectInput.

        The outputs argument contains non-null output handles in either of the two cases: (i) all of the inputs are non-distributable (only one instance of a streamable operator that generates the final output) or (ii) the corresponding output is distributable (NodeModel.getOutputPortRoles(). Non-null output handles need to be filled by this method.

        Specified by:
        runFinal in class StreamableOperator
        Parameters:
        inputs - The input handles.
        outputs - The output handles (may contain null, see above).
        exec - The context for cancelation, progress reporting.
        Throws:
        Exception - Any exception to indicate an error, cancelation.
